{"body": "I understand it may make some use cases easier to deal with, but I still don't think, as @steveklabnik commented, that's AR's job to handle wrapping itself. I'd rather stick with `map/collect` because I think it's more intention revealing and easier for someone new to the code, since it's a very simple and well known structure.\n\nAnyway, lets wait for some more people to give feedback. Thanks @al2o3cr!", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/8389089", "created_at": "2012-09-08T16:05:41Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7520#issuecomment-8389089", "updated_at": "2012-09-08T16:05:41Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7520, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/carlosantoniodasilva", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F60b997fd68261ce70cadaf6c8226c042.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/received_events", "gravatar_id": "77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "carlosantoniodasilva", "type": "User", "id": 26328, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237fac1bd3543c15100b6b1"}, "id": 8389089, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7520"}
